Ford History
Ford offers several car, truck and SUV models. Ford prices for all models fall within the starting price range of $13,995 to $49,325.
In October of 1913, Henry Ford changed the world of car production with the mass production of the Ford Model T. The new car assembly line helped reduce Ford prices and helped make personal transportation affordable. The moving assembly line reduced the time to assemble the chassis by more than 10 hours per car. With this new assembly line, Ford produced 308,162 cars, which was more than all other auto makers combined.
Ford is also responsible for the best-selling U.S. sports car and convertible, the Mustang. Ford trucks have been extremely successful with model lines such as the Ford F-Series, which has been the best selling full-sized pickup truck for more than 30 years. The company now offers crossovers as well as Ford SUV models.
TrueCar is an independent service provider that improves the car buying experience by collecting, analyzing, and presenting vehicle data from multiple sources. Although TrueCar provides new car pricing information and other data with respect to most vehicles on the market, TrueCar remains independent and is not affiliated with, sponsored by, or endorsed by Ford. All use of Ford's trademarks, brands, and logos, including all Ford marks displayed here, is purely referential, and such marks are the property of Ford. TrueCar makes no claim of ownership in such marks, and no claim of affiliation with Ford. TrueCar provides information about Ford car prices, but does not sell cars, automobile parts, or automobile repair services.






