Chevrolet History
New Chevrolet models have starting prices that range from $12,685 to $51,670. Besides the Corvette, Chevrolet prices tend to stay under $26,000 starting. Chevy models such as SUVs, trucks and vans tend to be more expensive and fall into the $17,000 to $52,000 starting price range.
Chevrolet, also known as Chevy is General Motors highest-selling brand of vehicle to date. Chevrolet was founded by Louis Chevrolet a racecar driver and William Durant (who was the founder of GM). Chevrolet Motor Car Co. was incorporated in November 1911 and then acquired by GM in 1917.
In 1913, Chevy started using its "bowtie emblem." In the 1950's and 1960's Chevrolet had ha great influence on the American automobile market. The Chevrolet small-block V-8 design was released in 1955. It is still produced today making it the the longest mass-produced engine in the world.
TrueCar is an independent service provider that improves the car buying experience by collecting, analyzing, and presenting vehicle data from multiple sources. Although TrueCar provides new car pricing information and other data with respect to most vehicles on the market, TrueCar remains independent and is not affiliated with, sponsored by, or endorsed by Chevrolet. All use of Chevrolet's trademarks, brands, and logos, including all Chevrolet marks displayed here, is purely referential, and such marks are the property of Chevrolet. TrueCar makes no claim of ownership in such marks, and no claim of affiliation with Chevrolet. TrueCar provides information about Chevrolet car prices, but does not sell cars, automobile parts, or automobile repair services.






